  "text": "The HTTP filter chain lifecycle spans two repos. **Proto schema**: `HttpConnectionManager` in data-plane-api defines `repeated HttpFilter http_filters` (line 471) and the `HttpFilter` message (line 1339). **Config-time registration**: `HttpConnectionManagerConfig` (config.h/cc) implements `FilterChainFactory` and uses `FilterChainHelper::processFilters` to iterate the proto's `http_filters`, look up each factory by type, call `createFilterFactoryFromProto`, and store `FilterFactoryCb` closures in a `FilterFactoriesList`. **Chain construction**: When a new stream arrives, `ConnectionManagerImpl` (conn_manager_impl.cc:785) passes the `FilterChainFactory` to `DownstreamFilterManager`. `FilterManager::createFilterChain()` (filter_manager.cc:1550) calls `FilterChainFactory::createFilterChain`, which delegates to `FilterChainUtility::createFilterChainForFactories` (filter_chain_helper.cc:17). This iterates the stored factories and calls `FilterChainManager::applyFilterFactoryCb`, which is implemented by `FilterManager` itself (filter_manager.h:697) to instantiate `ActiveStreamDecoderFilter`/`ActiveStreamEncoderFilter` wrappers. **Runtime execution**: `FilterManager` drives `decodeHeaders/decodeData/decodeTrailers` and encode counterparts through the linked lists of `ActiveStreamDecoderFilter`/`ActiveStreamEncoderFilter`, checking `FilterHeadersStatus`/`FilterDataStatus` to control iteration.",
